      <div class="topic students">
        <h2>Students Learn How To:</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Navigate the career and major exploration processes</li>
          <li>Enhance self-awareness through self-assessments</li>
          <li>Discover career options and specific majors available at Auburn University</li>
          <li>Utilize a variety of resources to explore and gather information needed to make an informed decision</li>
          <li>Evaluate career options based on professional interests, personality, skills, and values</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="topic parents">
        <h2>Parents Learn:</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>How your student's brain is developing as they prepare for and enter college, and the impact this developmental stage has on their decision making</li>
          <li>About academics at Auburn – policies, majors/minors, resources</li>
          <li>About resources and tools that will help your student make informed and practical decisions about their future career</li>
          <li>About the AU Career Center services and resources available to your student</li>
          <li>How you can support your student’s career development as they are choosing a major and career</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
